Created on behalf of customer:
{quote}
As we know, If pageA links to pageB by referring to pageB's title, pageB's Info -> Incoming Links section can list pageA as an incoming link. But if pageA creates the link by pageB's pageId, using syntax like
{noformat}
[$1736795]
or
[Check this article|$1736795]
{noformat}
then incoming link fails to work.

I think using pageId to create a link is a very good practice, especially when the target page has a very long title, or the target page constantly changes his title. You know, if a pageB changes its title and you link to him by his title, then every change of the title will cause pageA's content to be modified - which may not be desired.

Would you consider fixing this problem?
{quote}

